OL,3,CCouple retire from running village
OL,4,CPost Office after more than 40 years
OL,6,FThere has been a Post Office in
OL,7,FMeliden for more than a century. But
OL,8,Fthis week marked the end of an era.
OL,10,FDennis and Meryl O'Donnell have run
OL,11,Fthe Post Office for 40 years but now
OL,12,Fthey have decided it is time to retire.
OL,14,FLocals gathered outside to give them a
OL,15,Fsend-off and thank them for their
OL,16,Fdedication to the community.
OL,18,FThey were given three cheers but there
OL,19,Fwere also shouts of "don't go!"
